h3#list-options List options
.ch-clearfix
	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-leftcolumn
			h4 Demo
			iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/list-options", style="height:180px")

	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-rightcolumn
			h4 Markup
			p
				| It's equal to 
				a(href="#lists") Lists
				|  but it groups the elements and improve the anchor navigation with an arrow. Also, exists chance to add icons.
			p
				| Just add the 
				code ch-list-options
				|  classname:
			pre
				| <ul class="ch-list-options">
				| 	<li class="ch-icon-leaf">
				| 		<a href="#">Including an icon and an anchor</a>
				| 	</li>
				| 	<li>
				| 		<a href="#">Including only an anchor</a>
				| 	</li>
				| 	<li>Just a list element</li>
				| </ul>

h3#transitions Transitions
.ch-clearfix
	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-leftcolumn
			h4 Demo
			iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/transitions", height="190")

	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-rightcolumn
			h4 Markup
			p
				strong Inline transition:
			p It can be used on any place you want, for example next to a button.
			p
				|Just add the 
				code ch-loading
				|  class to any element, this way:
			pre <span class="ch-loading">Loading...</span>
			p
				strong Block transition:
			p It's the major transition. It blocks all the screen with a dimmer and appears centered on document.
			p
				| You need to create a wrapper with the classname 
				code ch-loading-wrap
				|  and an internal element with the 
				code ch-loading-text
				|  that includes a legend, for example:
			pre
				| <div class="ch-loading-wrap">
				| 	<p class="ch-loading-text">Loading...</p>
				| </div>

h3#tags Tags
.ch-clearfix
	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-leftcolumn
			h4 Demo
			iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/tags", style="height:40px")

	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-rightcolumn
			h4 Markup
			p You can use this tags for example when there's applied filters on a search results.
			p The tags are preferently anchors, because when the user clicks on it, he'll be redirected to a new page without that tag.
			p
				| Just add a 
				code ch-tag
				|  class to any element and enjoy:
			pre <a class="ch-tag" href="#">Chico</a>

h3#pagination Pagination
.ch-clearfix
	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-leftcolumn
			h4 Demo
			iframe.mobile-demo(src="/mobile/demos/pagination", style="height:50px")

	.ch-g1-2
		.ch-rightcolumn
			h4 Markup
			p
				| You can convert any list into a Pagination by adding the 
				code ch-pagination
				|  classname.
			p
				| To specify the current selected page, add the 
				code ch-pagination-current
				|  class to the list element.
			p
				| Be sure to add the 
				code type
				|  attribute to 
				strong previous
				|  and 
				strong next
				|  anchors reference, and set 
				code prev
				|  and 
				code next
				|  as value, this way:
			pre
				| <ul class="ch-pagination">
				| 	<li><a type="prev" href="#">Prev</a></li>
				| 	<li><a href="#">1</a></li>
				| 	<li class="ch-pagination-current"><a href="#">2</a></li>
				| 	<li><a href="#">3</a></li>
				| 	<li><a type="next" href="#">Next</a></li>
				| </ul>

